<P><FONT SIZE=3 COLOR=#FF6600><B>Introduction </B></FONT><P><P>

The bard class is different than any other class in Everquest, and it's not for everyone. You can't heal like clerics, can't fight like warriors and monks, and you most certainly cannot burn like wizards. However, you can do a little of each. Bards are the 'jack of all trades, but master of none' class in Everquest. Bards are also not the most powerful class in a duel, or player killer mode. Therefore, if you wish to kill everyone that crosses your path, then go investigate the other classes. Bards do, however, have some unique abilities that make them a very attractive class.

<P><FONT SIZE=3 COLOR=#FF6600><B>Reasons to choose a Bard</B></FONT><P><P>

There are two major reasons to play a Bard in Everquest. Bards are a grouping magnetic. Everyone loves bards and their abilities, so you'll be constantly asked to join up with your fellow adventurers. Whereas warriors and wizards are shouting their requests to find groups, bards will receive personal tells inquiring  about their availability. It sure is nice to feel wanted! The second reason is kind of sad. Everquest was shipped with some very annoying game play 'features'. The Bard is the class which best neutralizes most of these boring aspects. 

<P><FONT SIZE=3 COLOR=#FF6600><B>Corpse Issues</B></FONT><P><P>

When a player dies, he leaves behind his corpse, and with it all his equipment, in the unfortunate location People new to Everquest won't have a clue how to find the corpse to retrieve their equipment. Even experienced players run into corpse issues now and again. The bard, at level four, receives a song that will point you straight towards the target corpse. That's right, a bard will never stress over corpse retrieval!

<P><FONT SIZE=3 COLOR=#FF6600><B>Travelling Issues</B></FONT><P><P>

The land of Norath is simply huge! Reaching a dungeon, or another town four zones away can take forever and a day. Fifth level bards have access to accelerando. This song vastly increases the groups running speed, and cuts down on those travel times immensely. Bards who attempt to play other characters will often comment on the "snail speed" of non-bard classes. 

<P><FONT SIZE=3 COLOR=#FF6600><B>Downtime Issues</B></FONT><P><P>

Players regenerate one hit point per tick, two while sitting down. Groups without clerics, and other healing classes, will have some major downtime issues after a particularly brutal battle. Even with healers, groups must wait until the healers have meditated enough mana to heal the front line tanks. Enter the bard! Hymn of Restoration, received at level 6, speeds up the healing rate. It starts off adding +2 hit points per tick to the healing rate of each group member, and +4 while a stringed instrument is being played. These numbers even increase as your singing and stringed instruments skills rise! From soloing to participating in huge groups, bards don't spend much time sitting down. 

<P><FONT SIZE=3 COLOR=#FF6600><B>Other Issues</B></FONT><P><P>

Bards also receive the following songs that effect the entire group: invisibility, underwater breathing, and increased mana regeneration. Invisibility gets the party past nearly invincible guards, breathing allows exploration of the water, and mana regeneration leads to less downtime through healers and wizards that are ready to burn earlier.
